*   **Dependency on External Interfaces:** The security of this class is entirely reliant on the implementation of `v.b`. If `v.b` is implemented by a weak custom hashing algorithm (e.g., a simple XOR or iterative salt), the "signature" part of the `DataCacheKey` will be trivial to spoof.
*   **Insecure Cache Keys:** If this key is used to index encrypted transaction data, an attacker who can predict or craft these keys can force the application to retrieve their own malicious "cached" data instead of legitimate server responses.

